					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Turns out there wasn't much in the script incompatible with Python 2.x. The only problem (known) was that I was relying on Python 3's default behavior of outputting a float value when you divide one integer by another. The fix was to add .0 in the values in the NTSC and PAL tempo calculations.<br /><br />Hamtaro---should work in Python 2.x now, let me know if you try it out (re-uploaded the distro in the OP, with description of change in the readme file)</div>

